data.enText: to send an electronic signal, radio or television broadcast, etc.

data.chText: 典礼通过卫星向五十多个国家进行了实况转播。
data.enText: The ceremony was transmitted live by satellite to over fifty countries.

data.chText: 收发两用的短波无线电装置
data.enText: a short-wave radio that can transmit as well as receive
to pass sth from one person to another

data.chText: 父母自己的恐惧有可能在无意中感染了孩子。
data.enText: Parents can unwittingly transmit their own fears to their children.

data.chText: 传（热、声等）；透（光等）；使通过
data.enText: to allow heat, light, sound, etc. to pass through

simple_means.memory_skill: trans 横过 + mit 送，放出 → 跨距离传达、寄送 → 传达

tr: broadcast over the airwaves, as in radio or television
example: We cannot air this X-rated song

tr: send from one person or place to another
transmit or serve as the medium for transmission

value.def: When radio and television programmes, computer data, or other electronic messages are transmitted, they are sent from one place to another, using wires, radio waves, or satellites.

example.ex: The game was transmitted live in Spain and Italy...
example.tran: 这场比赛在西班牙和意大利进行了现场直播。

example.ex: The information is electronically transmitted to schools and colleges…
example.tran: 信息通过电子方式传送到各所学校和学院。

example.ex: This is currently the most efficient way to transmit certain types of data like electronic mail...
example.tran: 这是目前传送电子邮件等某些类型的数据的最高效方式。

example.ex: The device is not designed to transmit to satellites.
example.tran: 该设备不是为向卫星发送信号而设计的。

value.def: If one person or animal transmits a disease to another, they have the disease and cause the other person or animal to have it.

example.tran: 传染疾病给人类的蚊子

example.ex: There was no danger of transmitting the infection through operations.
example.tran: 不存在通过手术传播这种传染病的风险。

value.def: If you transmit an idea or feeling to someone else, you make them understand and share the idea or feeling.

example.ex: The message they are transmitting to their daughters is very different from that of previous generations…
example.tran: 他们向女儿传输的信息与上几代人截然不同。

example.ex: He transmitted his keen enjoyment of singing to the audience.
example.tran: 他把自己对演唱的激情投入传递给了观众。

value.def: If an object or substance transmits something such as sound or electrical signals, the sound or signals are able to pass through it.

example.ex: These thin crystals transmit much of the power...
example.tran: 这些薄薄的晶体传导了大部分的动力。

example.ex: There was no vibration transmitted to the handles and the machine wasn't noisy either.
example.tran: 没有任何振动传导到手柄，机器也没有任何噪音。
